General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (8) Collection and reporting by a national securities association that is registered
2 pursuant to 15 U.S.C. § 78o-3, any regulations adopted under it, or any
3 information that the national securities association is required to provide
4 pursuant to State law.
5 (9) Requests by the Attorney General for personal information required for an
6 audit, examination, review, or investigation pursuant to Chapters 36C, 36E,
7 55A, 75, and 131F of the General Statutes. Personal information provided
8 pursuant to this exception shall only be used in connection with the specific
9 audit, examination, review, or investigation to which the request relates and
10 for any related proceedings. Any personal information collected shall
11 otherwise remain subject to the provisions of G.S. 55A-18-04(a)(2), unless
12 expressly required by law to be publicly disclosed.
13 "§ 55A-18-06. Penalties.
14 (a) A person alleging a violation of this Article may bring a civil action for appropriate
15 injunctive relief, damages, or both. Damages awarded under this section may include one of the
16 following, as appropriate:
17 (1) A sum of money not less than two thousand five hundred dollars ($2,500) to
18 compensate for injury or loss caused by each violation of this Article.
19 (2) For an intentional violation of this Article, a sum of money not to exceed three
20 times the sum described in subdivision (1) of this subsection.
21 (b) A court, in rendering a judgment in an action brought under this Article, may award
22 all or a portion of the costs of litigation, including reasonable attorneys' fees and witness fees, to
23 the complainant in the action if the court determines that the award is appropriate.
24 (c) A person who knowingly violates this Article is guilty of a Class 2 misdemeanor.
25 "§ 55A-18-07. Severability.
26 If any provision of this Article or its application to any person or circumstance is held invalid,
27 then the invalidity shall not affect other provisions or applications of this Article that can be given
28 effect without the invalid provision or application and, to that end, the provisions of this Article
29 shall be severable."
30 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective December 1, 2025, and applies to offenses
31 committed on or after that date.
